# CVE: CVE-2026-0861
# Package: glibc (GNU C Library)
# Severity: HIGH
# CVSS Score: 7.5
# Description: Integer overflow in memalign suite of functions
# 
# Exception Details:
# - Type: Risk Accepted
# - Justification: Limited exploitability - requires attacker control of both
#   size and alignment arguments. Alignment values are typically constrained
#   and not user-controlled in this application.
# - Compensating Controls: Application does not expose memory allocation
#   parameters to external input
# 
# Remediation Plan:
# - Monitor: Debian/Python base image updates
# - Action: Update base image when glibc 2.43+ is available
# - Alternative: Consider Alpine base image (uses musl instead of glibc)
